---------------------------------------------------------------
MEFISTO software        English Version        December 2008
---------------------------------------------------------------
The menu of mesh drawings has been modified at level of
Points, Lines, Surfaces, Volumes and Objects.
NEWS:
MAILLER
- Option 16 of surfaces: a QUADRANGULER along
  the normal vectors of a profile line
- Option 19 of surfaces: a TRIANGULER by adding of
  the barycentre of triangles with same data input as 9;
- Option 26 of 2d surfaces: a MODIFIER of a plane mesh
  by mouse clicks 
- Option 33 of volumes: An HEXAHEDRISER of a
  CUBE or a SPHERE
- Option 4 of drawings of Volumes: Drawing of Finite
  Element of a volume cut by a plane
- Option 5 of drawings of Objects: Drawing of Finite
  Element of an object cut by a plane
- Option 16 of drawings of gradients, fluxes, stresses:
  Drawing of arrows to represent gradients, fluxes or
  stresses of Finite Elements of an object cut by a plane
- Option 39 subdivide any triangle or quadrangle of the
  initial mesh into 4 sub elements of same type
- Addition of MULTI-MATERIALS VOLUMES (one materiau=one volume)
  An union of several volumes is a MULTI-MATERIALS VOLUME.
  A type 9 volume with several type 8 volumes is a 
  MULTI-MATERIALS VOLUME.
  The surfaces, interfaces between 2 materials are drawn.
- Volume 15 by rotation of a meshed surface:
  The restriction of no vertices of the boundary on the
  axis has been deleted by creation of pyramids
- Volume 19 a TETRAHEDRIZER by adding of the barycentre
  of triangles with same data input as volume 9;
- Volume 31 the tetrahedrization cuts the pyramida (from
  volume 15), the pentahedra and the hexahedra.
  If the volume is MULTI-MATERIALS, the materials which
  constitute it, are tetrahedrized and their previous meshes
  with pyramids, pentahedra, hexahedra are replaced.
  This replacement permit the compatibility of triangles
  on the interfaces, limits of 2 materials.
- Volume 39 subdivide any tetrahedron into 8 sub-tetra
  any pentahedron into 8 sub-penta, any hexahedron into 8
  sub-hexa and pyramida into 6 sub-pyra and 4 sub-tetra
ELASTICER:
- Drawing of Von Mises or Tresca's plasticity criterion
FLUIDER
- Solution of the steady and unsteady STOKES problem for
  an incompressible fluid by Taylor-Hood or Brezzi-Fortin
  finite elements
